WEBVTT

00:27.911 --> 00:29.879
(STATIC)

01:29.039 --> 01:31.530
(STATIC FADING IN AND OUT)

01:36.546 --> 01:38.707
(GHOSTLY SCREAMS)

02:10.280 --> 02:12.510
(STATIC AND SNATCHED VOICES)

02:15.585 --> 02:18.909
(MUSIC PLAYS ON RADIO)

02:18.989 --> 02:22.212
'More rain tomorrow
with the chance of thunderstorms...'

02:22.292 --> 02:25.455
(STATIC AND STATIONS FADING IN AND OUT)

02:57.761 --> 03:00.750
MAN: Mikey, quit playing,
get ready for school.

03:00.830 --> 03:04.454
Come on, start eating. Your mom's
gonna pick you up in 10 minutes.

03:04.534 --> 03:06.990
(TUNES RADIO IN)

03:07.070 --> 03:09.593
- Hey, were you messing with this?
- No.

03:09.673 --> 03:11.695
No! Bet you were.

03:11.775 --> 03:14.564
- I bet you were fooling around.
- (PHONE)

03:14.644 --> 03:16.612
- I'll get it.
- All right.

03:18.548 --> 03:20.103
Hello.

03:20.183 --> 03:21.338
Hi, Jane.

03:21.418 --> 03:23.540
- Mikey, you want more juice?
- Sure.

03:23.620 --> 03:26.776
- Here you go.
- Yeah, no problem.

03:26.856 --> 03:28.915
OK. See ya.

03:30.160 --> 03:32.415
- Jane can't make it.
- Why not?

03:32.495 --> 03:35.051
- She didn't say.
- Didn't say what?

03:35.131 --> 03:39.222
- Your mom can't pick you up.
- Does that mean I miss school?

03:39.302 --> 03:42.499
No! It means I take you instead.

03:43.406 --> 03:45.374
Nice try, tiger.

03:47.444 --> 03:49.605
It was a nice try, though.

03:59.222 --> 04:01.611
- Where you going, baby?
- My publishers.

04:01.691 --> 04:03.852
They're gonna show me the cover.

04:05.095 --> 04:07.086
Wow. You look great.

04:09.132 --> 04:11.123
You look really great.

04:12.435 --> 04:14.494
You look really, really great.

04:17.107 --> 04:19.870
No, John, we're late already.

04:21.678 --> 04:25.637
And you have toothpaste
on your mouth. Right there.

04:35.525 --> 04:37.823
- You OK?
- Yeah.

04:42.432 --> 04:45.121
- You sure?
- Well, I might be...

04:45.201 --> 04:47.999
more than OK.

04:50.106 --> 04:52.662
Oh, my God in heaven.

04:52.742 --> 04:55.939
Yes! Yes, yes!

04:59.049 --> 05:01.071
This could be wrong. I'll do another one.

05:01.151 --> 05:03.573
- Let's tell Mike he's getting a brother.
- Wait.

05:03.653 --> 05:06.576
I'll do another test and then see the doctor.

05:06.656 --> 05:09.022
Congratulations, honey.

05:16.733 --> 05:18.355
Lunch bag.

05:18.435 --> 05:20.357
Suit bag.

05:20.437 --> 05:22.098
Kiss.

05:23.206 --> 05:26.835
All right. See you in a couple of days.
Say hi to your mom.

05:27.777 --> 05:30.211
And you, take it easy.

05:31.781 --> 05:33.442
I know.

05:38.822 --> 05:41.382
- (ENGINE REVS)
- Hey!

05:46.096 --> 05:48.291
Bye. I love you.

05:49.099 --> 05:51.499
See you later. Don't worry.

05:53.937 --> 05:55.905
(CAR HORN)

05:59.442 --> 06:01.706
(DOG BARKING)

06:05.715 --> 06:07.706
(HELICOPTER)

06:12.021 --> 06:15.311
(ANIMATED CHATTER)

06:15.391 --> 06:17.655
- Hi, Kelvin.
- How you doing?

06:19.829 --> 06:21.451
- Mr. Rivers.
- Hey.

06:21.531 --> 06:24.421
Frank asked if you'd call
as soon as you're in.

06:24.501 --> 06:26.356
Oh. Sure.

06:26.436 --> 06:28.024
Wow.

06:28.104 --> 06:30.693
- Wow what?
- You. You're smiling.

06:30.773 --> 06:32.829
Is that a big deal that I'm smiling?

06:32.909 --> 06:35.031
- It is on a Monday morning, yeah.
- Really?

06:35.111 --> 06:37.067
- Really.
- OK.

06:37.147 --> 06:39.402
- Yeah.
- Hey, Karen,

06:39.482 --> 06:43.073
order me a bouquet of flowers
for the end of the day, lilies.

06:43.153 --> 06:47.077
And champa... No, not champagne,
get me chocolates.

06:47.157 --> 06:49.813
Those Belgian kind.

06:49.893 --> 06:52.088
You know? What are you looking at?

06:53.630 --> 06:55.621
Something's up.

06:57.300 --> 06:59.656
- Something's really up.
- Would you just...

06:59.736 --> 07:02.225
- I'm going.
- Thank you.

07:02.305 --> 07:04.569
- But I know something's up.
- Frank.

07:08.811 --> 07:10.779
Hey, babe, are you home?

07:24.827 --> 07:26.583
'You have one message.

07:26.663 --> 07:32.522
'Message received Monday 16th, 6:07pm.'

07:32.602 --> 07:36.826
'Hey, honey, it's me.
So Julie's having trouble with Ben, again.'

07:36.906 --> 07:39.829
- What's new?
- 'So I said I'd have a drink with her.

07:39.909 --> 07:44.167
'Don't worry, I'll stick to water,
and I'll call when I'm on my way home.

07:44.247 --> 07:47.273
'Did you see the demo cover?
What do you think?

07:48.718 --> 07:50.709
'I was kind of thinking...'

07:52.689 --> 07:54.911
(STATIC ON ANSWER MACHINE)

07:54.991 --> 07:56.652
'No messages.'

08:01.564 --> 08:05.091
(STATIC)

08:07.870 --> 08:10.634
(ONLY STATIC)

08:12.275 --> 08:14.436
(MUSIC STARTS)

08:30.493 --> 08:34.683
'Hi, it's Anna. Leave a message
after the beep and I will call you back.'

08:34.764 --> 08:37.520
Hi, it's me, it's a little before midnight.

08:37.600 --> 08:39.722
I guess you're still with Julie.

08:39.802 --> 08:44.092
Give me a call, let me know.
All right? Love you, bye.

08:44.173 --> 08:46.563
'Hi, it's Julie. Leave a message.'

08:46.643 --> 08:48.965
Julie, hi, it's John. Do me a favor.

08:49.045 --> 08:53.102
When you get this message,
have Anna give me a call.

08:53.182 --> 08:56.549
I guess you guys are having
a good time. Thank you.

08:59.389 --> 09:00.981
(CLOCK TICKING)

09:20.443 --> 09:22.104
(DOOR SLAMS)

09:58.715 --> 10:01.104
(RADIO SUDDENLY COMES ON, LOUD)

10:01.184 --> 10:04.984
(STATIC AND VOICES
AS RADIO TUNES THROUGH STATIONS)

10:15.832 --> 10:18.421
NEWSREADER: '...victim of a tragic accident.

10:18.501 --> 10:21.124
'Police have discovered
the heel of a woman's shoe

10:21.204 --> 10:24.327
'close to her abandoned car on Argyle Avenue.

10:24.407 --> 10:28.698
'She may have slipped into the river
while attending to a flat tire.

10:28.778 --> 10:31.467
'Although divers
are still searching the area,

10:31.547 --> 10:33.703
'reported sightings
of the best-selling author

10:33.783 --> 10:37.774
'continue to reach police
from towns up to 20 miles away.

10:37.854 --> 10:40.910
'Police are keeping an open mind
as to her whereabouts.

10:40.990 --> 10:45.915
'Anna Rivers' latest novel The Eternal Wait
is scheduled for release this fall

10:45.995 --> 10:48.184
'and her husband, architect Jonathan Rivers,

10:48.264 --> 10:52.922
'is said to be taking time out to
accompany her on her promotional tour.'

10:53.002 --> 10:55.258
- We're gonna get going.
- OK.

10:55.338 --> 10:57.272
Come on, Michael.

10:58.207 --> 11:01.631
- Mark'll be home in a minute, so...
- OK. OK.

11:01.711 --> 11:04.434
- Come on, pal, say goodbye to your dad.
- Come here.

11:04.514 --> 11:08.109
Be a good boy. Take care of your mom.
Go get your stuff.

11:10.486 --> 11:13.009
Hey, there's a bed at our place
if you want it.

11:13.089 --> 11:17.025
Oh, thanks. Jane,
you don't have to put yourself out for me.

11:20.263 --> 11:22.254
I know I wasn't a very good...

11:27.670 --> 11:29.331
OK.

11:33.976 --> 11:39.437
WOMAN: 'It's ten days now since international
author Anna Rivers' car was found...'

11:40.516 --> 11:43.706
MAN: 'Although police still suspect
she could have drowned,

11:43.786 --> 11:47.009
'they are not ruling out
the possibility of abduction.

11:47.089 --> 11:51.082
'Architect husband Jonathan Rivers
spoke of his anguish today...'

11:53.429 --> 11:57.253
WOMAN: 'Three weeks since
the disappearance of author Anna Rivers...'

11:57.333 --> 12:01.861
MAN: 'Police say they are constructing
a profile of a likely abductor.'

12:03.239 --> 12:05.995
WOMAN:
'Distraught husband, Jonathan Rivers...'

12:06.075 --> 12:10.011
MAN: '...had this message for anyone
who may know of her whereabouts.'

12:10.947 --> 12:13.438
JOHN: 'It's, er, difficult.

12:14.851 --> 12:18.174
'But you never give up hope, ever.

12:18.254 --> 12:20.245
'It's the only way to get by.'

13:25.321 --> 13:29.579
I got 50 guys and thousands of dollars'
worth of equipment waiting,

13:29.659 --> 13:33.151
so if you want to tell them
to wait a month, call me.

14:23.679 --> 14:25.935
- My goodness.
- You were outside my house.

14:26.015 --> 14:28.571
- I'm sorry.
- You were outside my house

14:28.651 --> 14:30.907
and now you're outside my office.

14:30.987 --> 14:34.544
Don't insult my intelligence
by telling me that's a coincidence.

14:34.624 --> 14:37.024
No, it's no coincidence.

14:38.094 --> 14:39.749
Do I know you?

14:39.829 --> 14:41.820
My name is Raymond Price.

14:43.165 --> 14:47.323
- Are you following me?
- It's about Anna, Mr. Rivers.

14:47.403 --> 14:51.396
I've been receiving messages from her,
from the other side.

14:53.542 --> 14:56.032
From what other side?

14:56.112 --> 14:57.667
Jonathan...

14:57.747 --> 14:59.874
your wife is dead.

15:07.256 --> 15:08.556
I have proof, Mr. Rivers.

15:08.656 --> 15:11.851
She's been trying to communicate
ever since the moment of her death.

15:12.151 --> 15:16.619
Look, Mr. Rivers, my son died when he was 12.

15:16.699 --> 15:20.256
- For years I've been suicidal.
- Look. Just stay away from me.

15:20.336 --> 15:24.026
But then someone told me
what I have told you.

15:24.106 --> 15:26.963
That my son, my dead son, had made contact.

15:27.043 --> 15:30.733
And he had, Mr. Rivers, it was true.
From the other side.

15:30.813 --> 15:32.702
And he was happy. Happy.

15:32.782 --> 15:35.910
Please. Yes. And also at ease.

15:36.786 --> 15:39.775
And it changed my life, Mr. Rivers,

15:39.855 --> 15:41.982
because then, then I knew.

15:43.559 --> 15:45.448
So please, please, Mr. Rivers,

15:45.528 --> 15:48.184
put this in a drawer, hide it,
forget about it,

15:48.264 --> 15:51.220
but please don't throw it away.

15:51.300 --> 15:53.359
Because, one day...

15:54.637 --> 15:56.662
you will want to know.

15:59.608 --> 16:01.633
My thoughts are with you both.

16:14.790 --> 16:17.480
JOHN: 'It's Anna Rivers.

16:17.560 --> 16:20.449
'The fabulous Anna Rivers
carrying groceries.'

16:20.529 --> 16:23.452
- 'Stop it.'
- 'How was shopping?'

16:23.532 --> 16:25.554
- 'Turn it off.'
- 'OK. Just...

16:25.634 --> 16:28.658
- 'There's one of her best features.'
- 'Shut up.'

16:28.738 --> 16:31.866
'That's a beautiful thing,
ladies and gentlemen.'

16:59.769 --> 17:01.930
(KNOCKING)

17:09.545 --> 17:12.105
(KNOCKING)

17:38.107 --> 17:41.664
WOMAN: 'The body of internationally
renowned author Anna Rivers

17:41.744 --> 17:46.168
'was discovered last night by a security
guard making a routine visit...'

17:46.248 --> 17:49.405
MAN: '...to the disused pier 16,
three miles upriver

17:49.485 --> 17:51.741
'from where her car was found abandoned

17:51.821 --> 17:54.510
'five weeks ago on Argyle Avenue.

17:54.590 --> 17:56.545
'The discovery brings to an end...'

17:56.625 --> 17:58.147
MAN: 'Before she drowned,

17:58.227 --> 18:03.686
'your wife sustained injuries consistent
with a fall onto the rocks by the river.

18:03.766 --> 18:07.896
'The damage to the head,
the break to the arm.

18:10.673 --> 18:14.630
'When the tide came in, she would have been
unable to help herself.

18:14.710 --> 18:18.234
'She would have been swept upstream
several miles.

18:18.314 --> 18:20.782
'I'm so sorry for your loss.'

18:28.724 --> 18:31.714
WOMAN: 'Divers recovered
her personal effects.

18:31.794 --> 18:35.251
'Her cell phone was in her car,
and we're returning it to you.'

18:35.331 --> 18:38.020
MAN:
...giving her to us, her family and friends,

18:38.100 --> 18:42.358
to know and to love as a companion
on our earthly pilgrimage.

18:42.438 --> 18:45.961
Give us faith to see in death
the gate of eternal life,

18:46.041 --> 18:50.232
so that in quiet confidence
we may continue our course on earth

18:50.312 --> 18:55.504
until, by Your call, we are reunited
with those who have gone before.

18:55.584 --> 18:57.245
- Amen.
- ALL: Amen.

19:26.282 --> 19:28.237
- So, what do you think?
- I love it.

19:28.317 --> 19:30.272
- Yeah?
- Yeah. It's nice here.

19:30.352 --> 19:32.708
- All right.
- It's a fresh start.

19:32.788 --> 19:34.449
I guess.

19:36.892 --> 19:39.081
Could you...

19:39.161 --> 19:41.629
Could you take Mikey for the weekend?

19:42.631 --> 19:44.997
Yeah, of course.

19:47.069 --> 19:49.333
Maybe... maybe a little longer.

19:50.572 --> 19:52.631
As long as you want, John.

20:10.659 --> 20:12.320
(SOBBING)

20:43.392 --> 20:45.587
WORKER: We're gonna go lay the floor now.

20:49.631 --> 20:53.022
- When are you gonna bring them?
- They'd like to see you this week.

20:53.102 --> 20:55.858
Sure. Fine, it shouldn't be any problem.

20:55.938 --> 20:58.928
(SHAKING AND RATTLING)

20:59.008 --> 21:00.729
BOTH: Whoops.

21:00.809 --> 21:06.368
MAN: (CHUCKLING) You brought me here
just to do that, didn't you?

21:06.448 --> 21:10.139
JOHN: No, I didn't.
Let me see what I can do here.

21:10.219 --> 21:14.622
MAN: This is where you tell me
you're running over budget, right?

21:19.261 --> 21:22.885
- (CELLPHONE RINGS)
- MAN: Shit. Keep doing that!

21:22.965 --> 21:24.694
I'm sorry, I didn't...

21:35.344 --> 21:38.245
Ask them if they have a light.

21:45.154 --> 21:47.543
- You guys OK?
- We are now.

21:47.623 --> 21:49.278
Yeah.

21:49.358 --> 21:53.021
I trust you'll fix this
before Mr. Cunningham arrives.

22:22.124 --> 22:24.115
(CELLPHONE RINGS)

22:38.874 --> 22:41.274
(CRACKLING)

22:43.178 --> 22:44.372
Anna?

22:52.221 --> 22:54.485
(SILENCE)

23:12.774 --> 23:14.401
(WHISPERING)

23:29.458 --> 23:31.050
ANNA: 'Jonathan.'

23:32.694 --> 23:34.685
(BEEPING)

23:50.879 --> 23:52.901
'You have one message.

23:52.981 --> 23:57.372
'Message received Wednesday 23rd,

23:57.452 --> 23:58.942
'2:30 am.'

24:00.189 --> 24:02.851
(CRACKLING AND STATIC)

24:04.660 --> 24:06.355
ANNA: 'Jonathan.'

24:07.396 --> 24:11.954
'End of message. You have no messages.'

24:12.034 --> 24:14.123
(BEEPING)

24:14.203 --> 24:16.694
'You have no messages.

24:19.575 --> 24:22.131
'You have no messages.'

24:22.211 --> 24:23.940
(BEEPING)

24:55.677 --> 24:57.872
(DOORBELL)

25:00.649 --> 25:03.641
Oh! Please, come. How nice.

25:05.354 --> 25:07.075
- Hello.
- Hi.

25:07.155 --> 25:10.179
- Look, er...
- I was just about to finish with someone.

25:10.259 --> 25:13.315
- I can come back.
- No, it won't take long.

25:13.395 --> 25:16.485
I'm really glad to see you.
I was hoping that you'd come.

25:16.565 --> 25:18.687
- Thank you.
- This is Sarah Tate.

25:18.767 --> 25:20.997
Let me introduce you to Mr. Rivers.

25:22.571 --> 25:24.927
Sorry, I'm a little...

25:25.007 --> 25:26.962
We've had a breakthrough today.

25:27.042 --> 25:29.164
It's incredible.

25:29.244 --> 25:31.007
It truly is.

25:33.849 --> 25:35.804
- This is ridiculous.
- Stay awhile.

25:35.884 --> 25:38.240
I should get these boxes back to the store.

25:38.320 --> 25:40.709
Sarah, there's no need to hurry.

25:40.789 --> 25:42.744
Make yourself a cup of tea.

25:42.824 --> 25:44.951
I suppose. Thank you.

25:45.894 --> 25:47.849
Would you like one?

25:47.929 --> 25:50.185
Yeah, that'd be great. Thank you.

25:50.265 --> 25:51.994
Thank you.

25:52.734 --> 25:54.565
Mr. Rivers, please.

25:58.273 --> 26:02.039
Oh, er... Excuse me. Please, sit here. Sit.

26:05.914 --> 26:09.577
So, have you heard of E.V.P., Mr. Rivers?

26:10.619 --> 26:11.974
No.

26:12.054 --> 26:15.344
I'm not surprised.
Those that have call us cranks.

26:15.424 --> 26:19.121
E.V.P. stands for
electronic voice phenomenon.

26:21.129 --> 26:23.118
- I'm listening.
- Well.

26:23.198 --> 26:26.321
I'm not a clairvoyant, I'm not a medium,

26:26.401 --> 26:28.023
I don't contact the dead,

26:28.103 --> 26:30.225
the dead contact me.

26:30.305 --> 26:32.398
And, with E.V.P.,

26:33.375 --> 26:35.297
I can hear them,

26:35.377 --> 26:38.005
I can see them, and...

26:39.247 --> 26:41.681
I can record them.

26:51.126 --> 26:53.248
(STATIC)

26:53.328 --> 26:55.523
(SNIPPETS OF SPEECH)

27:00.836 --> 27:02.827
'...I understand...'

27:08.377 --> 27:10.345
'...you shouldn't be...'

27:24.393 --> 27:27.658
- And they are...
- That's right.

27:28.630 --> 27:30.757
People that have passed over.

27:46.148 --> 27:49.371
Is this your job, or a hobby, or what?

27:49.451 --> 27:53.842
(LAUGHS) I think obsession
would be more appropriate, to be honest.

27:53.922 --> 27:55.944
Now, I wonder where... Ah!

27:56.024 --> 28:00.782
Here we are. They don't always
appear visually the first few times.

28:00.862 --> 28:05.620
We tend only to pick up their voices
and people can find that frustrating.

28:05.700 --> 28:07.522
But when it works,

28:07.602 --> 28:12.461
and you see the faces of the people
that you're able to help, like Sarah,

28:12.541 --> 28:17.205
nothing, believe me, nothing comes close.

28:19.548 --> 28:22.881
Mr. Rivers, do you want to hear your wife?

28:33.829 --> 28:35.990
Yes.

28:38.733 --> 28:41.327
(CRACKLING)

28:46.842 --> 28:48.810
'Jonathan.

28:55.550 --> 28:57.906
'Jonathan.

28:57.986 --> 28:59.715
'Find him.

29:02.591 --> 29:04.946
'Jonathan Rivers.

29:05.026 --> 29:07.017
'Find him.

29:08.897 --> 29:11.653
'Jonathan... Jonathan...

29:11.733 --> 29:13.555
'Rivers...

29:13.635 --> 29:16.195
'Find him, please.'

29:18.240 --> 29:20.208
(SOBBING)

29:37.259 --> 29:40.849
The frustrating thing about E.V.P.
is it's not live.

29:40.929 --> 29:42.617
You need to make the recording

29:42.697 --> 29:46.421
and you'll only know if you've got
results when you play it back.

29:46.501 --> 29:49.157
Here. It has milk.

29:49.237 --> 29:52.001
- Perfect. Thank you.
- Excuse me for a moment.

29:55.744 --> 29:58.033
It's an amazing feeling, isn't it?

29:58.113 --> 29:59.341
Er...

30:01.383 --> 30:02.838
It's indescribable.

30:02.918 --> 30:05.907
It took me a few visits to get
used to it but it's addictive.

30:05.987 --> 30:09.787
I'm here all the time. He's really helped me.

30:11.326 --> 30:15.183
I try to help him when I can,
so I keep some of this stuff at the store.

30:15.263 --> 30:17.925
- What store?
- I have a bookstore.

30:22.103 --> 30:25.197
Your wife was a wonderful writer, Mr. Rivers.

30:27.943 --> 30:29.774
Yeah.

30:32.814 --> 30:36.071
- So what made you come here?
- My fiancé.

30:36.151 --> 30:41.343
He died eight months ago. We've had
trouble deciphering what he's been saying

30:41.423 --> 30:43.357
but this afternoon we cracked it.

30:44.259 --> 30:46.750
Only two words - "Sarah, yes."

30:48.063 --> 30:52.254
Because, before he died, he promised me
that if it was like they say it is

30:52.334 --> 30:54.556
that he would find a way of getting to me

30:54.636 --> 30:57.628
and letting me know that he's happy.

30:58.807 --> 31:01.708
So, "Sarah, yes."

31:02.944 --> 31:04.411
Oh.

31:08.049 --> 31:11.712
Raymond thinks we probably won't
see him again now but that's OK.

31:14.122 --> 31:16.716
And I've heard what I wanted to hear.

31:22.430 --> 31:24.091
(THUNDER)

31:46.321 --> 31:47.982
(CRACKLING)

31:56.731 --> 31:58.460
Anna...

32:00.802 --> 32:02.565
this is John.

32:04.906 --> 32:08.637
